textDelta: Just like plants, ideas take nurturing in order to grow, while a neglected idea will wither.
Ideas are like plants because what you end up with is a bit unpredictable and not always what you imagined.
Ideas are like plants because you have to keep pruning away the unwanted offshoots and bad parts in order to have a successful outcome.
Ideas are like plants because some are tame and orderly, like trimmed hedges, and some grow wild and free like climbing vines and wildflowers.
Ideas are like plants because they both require hope; without hope no one would bother to plant a seed or try to come up with an idea whose outcome is unknown.
